1
00:00:39,810 --> 00:00:42,040
<i>[Jespipat Tilapornputt]</i>

2
00:00:42,040 --> 00:00:44,600
<i>[Nalinthip Sakulongumpai]</i>

3
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:04,920
<i>[Dear My Secretary]</i>

4
00:01:13,148 --> 00:01:15,166
- Let me go, Boss!
- I won't!

5
00:01:15,166 --> 00:01:16,366
Let me go!

6
00:01:16,366 --> 00:01:17,766
Let me go, Boss!

7
00:01:17,766 --> 00:01:19,500
- I won't!
- Let me go!

8
00:01:21,066 --> 00:01:24,000
- Let me go!
- I told you, I'm not letting you go!

9
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:24,710
<i>[Not approved]</i>

10
00:01:24,710 --> 00:01:25,960
<i>Let me go!</i>

11
00:01:26,633 --> 00:01:29,000
Boss! Let me go!

12
00:01:33,955 --> 00:01:35,350
Don't joke around like this, Boss!

13
00:01:35,350 --> 00:01:36,539
I'm not joking.

14
00:01:36,539 --> 00:01:39,747
I'm always serious, especially when it is about you.

15
00:01:39,747 --> 00:01:42,100
What is it with you, Secretary Prim?

16
00:01:42,966 --> 00:01:46,133
I just want to resign. Is that so wrong?

17
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:56,600
Fine. If you want to resign, go ahead and leave.

18
00:02:18,078 --> 00:02:23,262
<i>[Boss Wee-Woo!]</i>

19
00:02:23,262 --> 00:02:28,336
<i>[Boss Wee-Woo!]</i>

20
00:02:29,633 --> 00:02:31,233
Yes, Boss…

21
00:02:31,233 --> 00:02:35,633
<i>I was out running and thought you should come to run with me.</i>

22
00:02:36,368 --> 00:02:37,582
Running?

23
00:02:37,582 --> 00:02:40,948
<i>Yeah. Meet me at the park right now!</i>

24
00:02:40,948 --> 00:02:44,133
Okay. I'll go right away.

25
00:02:45,510 --> 00:02:47,110
<i>[5:00 AM]</i>

26
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:51,560
What kind of vision has come over him now…

27
00:03:32,733 --> 00:03:34,433
Keep up, Secretary Prim.

28
00:03:34,433 --> 00:03:36,033
Yes, Boss.

29
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:09,900
Sorry…

30
00:04:10,389 --> 00:04:12,533
How's it going, Secretary Prim?

31
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:17,366
I know that getting to run and absorbing the morning sunlight like this,

32
00:04:17,366 --> 00:04:22,400
it refreshes you, gets your blood pumping, and clears your mind. Am I right?

33
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:28,933
Yes, I feel full of energy and ready to work now.

34
00:04:28,933 --> 00:04:30,600
Perfect!

35
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,945
I had you exercise

36
00:04:31,945 --> 00:04:34,966
because walking up to the 4th floor the other day made you dead tired.

37
00:04:34,966 --> 00:04:40,066
You need to be stronger if you want to be my secretary for a long time.

38
00:04:40,066 --> 00:04:41,766
Got it?

39
00:04:41,766 --> 00:04:43,300
Yes, Boss.

40
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:49,250
<i>[7:10 Pace, 10:25]</i>

41
00:04:51,166 --> 00:04:54,966
But your pace is only 7. You're just power walking!

42
00:04:54,966 --> 00:04:58,009
I'll have to make you run every morning from now on.

43
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:06,200
This is just so…

44
00:05:07,633 --> 00:05:11,566
Radiant! Radiant! Radiant!

45
00:05:18,866 --> 00:05:20,432
Wear these, or you'll be dazzled.

46
00:05:20,432 --> 00:05:23,032
The sunlight has been strong in the morning lately.

47
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:27,066
You're the one who needs them.

48
00:05:27,066 --> 00:05:30,966
Because you're the one who's going to be dazzled by my brilliance.

49
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,133
It's such a burden having to be this way.

50
00:05:37,133 --> 00:05:40,233
But when someone shines this brightly, nothing can hold them back.

51
00:05:40,233 --> 00:05:41,879
Isn't that right, Secretary Prim?

52
00:05:41,879 --> 00:05:43,800
So cute!

53
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:45,500
That smile is so sweet.

54
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:48,400
How could anyone not fall in love with you?

55
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,966
Such beautiful fur, too.

56
00:05:50,966 --> 00:05:53,500
Now, let me see your paws, there we go.

57
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:56,866
So good! Very good!

58
00:05:56,866 --> 00:06:01,166
You don't bite, right? No biting, right? Good job, such a good one!

59
00:06:07,066 --> 00:06:08,380
I've rescheduled the Purchasing Department meeting

60
00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:10,540
to tomorrow noon, as instructed.

61
00:06:10,544 --> 00:06:13,033
At 11:00 a.m., there's an interview with the Asian Tomorrow page.

62
00:06:13,033 --> 00:06:14,833
They've requested 30 minutes.

63
00:06:14,833 --> 00:06:17,766
Including hair and makeup, which should take no more than an hour.

64
00:06:17,766 --> 00:06:21,033
As for the VIP zone planning meeting for the Countdown event,

65
00:06:21,033 --> 00:06:23,333
that's set for precisely 1:00 p.m.

66
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:27,500
After that, there's a discussion with…

67
00:06:35,166 --> 00:06:36,400
Secretary Prim.

68
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,100
Secretary Prim!

69
00:06:39,266 --> 00:06:40,866
Are you asleep right now?

70
00:06:41,466 --> 00:06:44,733
I'm sorry. I stayed up late last night.

71
00:06:44,733 --> 00:06:49,533
Should you get at least 7 to 8 hours daily for quality sleep?

72
00:06:49,533 --> 00:06:51,340
What exactly did you do?

73
00:06:53,870 --> 00:06:55,700
<i>[3:00 AM]</i>

74
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:02,436
<i>[Boss Wee-Woo!]</i>

75
00:07:02,436 --> 00:07:07,800
<i>[Boss Wee-Woo!]</i>

76
00:07:08,633 --> 00:07:10,566
<i>Yes, Boss.</i>

77
00:07:10,566 --> 00:07:15,300
<i>I want you to review the VIP guest list for the Countdown event again.</i>

78
00:07:15,300 --> 00:07:17,900
<i>All right. I'll send it to you tomorrow morning.</i>

79
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:21,300
<i>Review and send it tonight instead. I want to see it now.</i>

80
00:07:22,866 --> 00:07:24,766
<i>Okay…</i>

81
00:07:30,433 --> 00:07:32,433
<i>It's 3:00 a.m…</i>

82
00:07:47,866 --> 00:07:52,333
<i>I've sent it already, Boss. I'm going to sleep now, okay?</i>

83
00:08:07,666 --> 00:08:09,100
All right, I'll just continue then.

84
00:08:09,100 --> 00:08:11,295
After that, a meeting with Mr. Somphop,

85
00:08:11,295 --> 00:08:13,541
- regarding the Korean bag franchise deal that didn't go…
- Enough!

86
00:08:13,541 --> 00:08:17,266
I don't want a failure to ruin my mood first thing in the morning.

87
00:08:18,233 --> 00:08:20,233
A failure?

88
00:08:20,233 --> 00:08:25,366
But Mr. Somphop couldn't close the deal. That's all.

89
00:08:25,366 --> 00:08:27,900
In my work, there's no such thing as "that's all".

90
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:32,466
Will we let our competitor take this deal just because of that?

91
00:08:32,466 --> 00:08:35,490
If we don't aim for results, if we don't push to succeed,

92
00:08:35,490 --> 00:08:37,645
then what's the point of working?

93
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:42,333
All it takes is dedication and the will to succeed.

94
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:45,433
Why is that so hard for people to understand?

95
00:08:45,433 --> 00:08:48,266
Well, maybe because not everyone is like you, Boss.

96
00:08:48,266 --> 00:08:49,666
Perfect!

97
00:08:50,166 --> 00:08:53,833
Yes, no one's perfect except me.

98
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,033
Right.

99
00:08:55,033 --> 00:08:59,366
Boss, I've never met anyone as "absolutely perfect" as you.

100
00:09:14,666 --> 00:09:17,100
Thank you for dropping me off.

101
00:09:17,733 --> 00:09:19,900
Thank you, too, Yong.

102
00:09:21,340 --> 00:09:23,800
By the way, Mr. Khai sent over the outfit

103
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,400
for the Brazilian ambassador's birthday party.

104
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:29,033
I've already picked the Phthalo Green set with a black leather jacket for you.

105
00:09:29,033 --> 00:09:30,200
Hold on.

106
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:35,933
You pronounced the Phthola Green and black leather jacket wrong.

107
00:09:35,933 --> 00:09:37,766
Repeat it.

108
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:41,066
Phthalo Green.

109
00:09:41,066 --> 00:09:43,233
That accent is so local.

110
00:09:43,233 --> 00:09:44,400
Phthalo Green.

111
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:45,533
Phthalo Green.

112
00:09:45,533 --> 00:09:48,133
Not "Tha," it's Phthalo.

113
00:09:48,133 --> 00:09:50,766
- Phthalo.
- Phthalo.

114
00:09:50,766 --> 00:09:54,200
Phthalo, Phthalo Green.

115
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:56,400
- Thalo.
- Thalo.

116
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:57,966
Phthalo.

117
00:09:57,966 --> 00:10:00,866
Well, I don't have your perfect pronunciation, Boss.

118
00:10:02,833 --> 00:10:04,433
Fine.

119
00:10:05,900 --> 00:10:08,133
But even your Th isn't right.

120
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:12,200
You must touch your tongue to the top of your front teeth,

121
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:14,933
like this: Thuh.

122
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:16,033
Thuh.

123
00:10:16,033 --> 00:10:17,333
Stick the tongue out more.

124
00:10:17,333 --> 00:10:18,333
Thuh.

125
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:19,666
- Thuh.
- Thuh.

126
00:10:19,666 --> 00:10:21,400
More tongue!

127
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,900
- Thuh.
- Thuh.

128
00:10:22,900 --> 00:10:24,433
- Thuh.
- Thuh.

129
00:10:24,433 --> 00:10:25,766
Thuh.

130
00:10:25,766 --> 00:10:27,866
- Thuh.
- Thuh.

131
00:10:29,700 --> 00:10:31,833
- Thuh.
- Okay. That's correct.

132
00:10:31,833 --> 00:10:33,433
Perfect!

133
00:10:33,433 --> 00:10:35,166
Thank you.

134
00:10:35,166 --> 00:10:37,000
Good day.

135
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,933
Almost forgot.

136
00:10:39,933 --> 00:10:42,500
There's something personal I'd like to inform you about, Boss.

137
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:44,500
What is it?

138
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:46,000
I'm resigning.

139
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:50,300
I'm resigning. I'm resigning. I'm resigning.

140
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:55,100
So I wanted to let you know first.

141
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:58,000
I'll send you the resignation letter to sign later today.

142
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:04,633
- Yong.
- Yes, Boss?

143
00:11:04,633 --> 00:11:07,100
- Start the car.
- Yes, Boss.

144
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:15,333
- Yong.
- Yes, Boss?

145
00:11:15,333 --> 00:11:17,900
Did Prim just say she's resigning?

146
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:19,800
Yes, Boss. Resigning.

147
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:21,566
Resigning…

148
00:11:21,566 --> 00:11:23,633
Yes, Boss. Resigning.

149
00:11:31,066 --> 00:11:32,366
Boss? Did you forget something?

150
00:11:32,366 --> 00:11:34,566
Did you just say you were resigning?

151
00:11:34,566 --> 00:11:36,600
Yes. I'm resigning.

152
00:11:37,266 --> 00:11:39,433
- Yong!
- Yes, Boss?

153
00:11:54,166 --> 00:11:56,266
<i>She's resigning?</i>

154
00:11:56,266 --> 00:11:58,333
<i>Why would she resign?</i>

155
00:12:04,933 --> 00:12:08,100
<i>Or did I give her too much work?</i>

156
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:10,933
<i>But she's never complained about anything.</i>

157
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:14,420
<i>Did I accidentally do something wrong?</i>

158
00:12:14,420 --> 00:12:15,833
<i>No…</i>

159
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:18,333
<i>Someone like me, when have I ever done anything wrong?</i>

160
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:21,266
<i>What's going on with you, Secretary Prim?!</i>

161
00:12:22,900 --> 00:12:26,233
<i>I've finished organizing the contract documents!</i>

162
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:29,400
<i>This one for today's tie, okay?</i>

163
00:12:29,900 --> 00:12:31,633
<i>How about a tea break?</i>

164
00:12:31,633 --> 00:12:33,800
<i>The car is ready. This way, Boss.</i>

165
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:35,266
<i>Thank you for dropping me off, Boss.</i>

166
00:12:35,266 --> 00:12:37,233
<i>Thank you for teaching me everything, Boss.</i>

167
00:12:37,233 --> 00:12:38,166
<i>Thank you so much.</i>

168
00:12:38,166 --> 00:12:42,166
<i>Boss, I've never met anyone as absolutely perfect as you.</i>

169
00:12:42,166 --> 00:12:45,666
Come on! What's so bad about working with me?!

170
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:52,800
<i>Why am I even upset? Why am I even annoyed?</i>

171
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:55,566
<i>She's just a secretary. She wants to quit?</i>

172
00:12:55,566 --> 00:12:57,562
<i>It can happen all the time.</i>

173
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,733
<i>I'm resigning!</i>

174
00:13:25,433 --> 00:13:27,700
Secretary Prim…

175
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,466
Let's see.

176
00:13:32,620 --> 00:13:34,390
Hey, Meow-meow.

177
00:13:35,933 --> 00:13:38,266
Do you think he is going to be mad

178
00:13:38,266 --> 00:13:40,833
that I told him I'm resigning like that?

179
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:43,700
Will he understand?

180
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:47,533
But he has to understand, right?

181
00:13:47,533 --> 00:13:51,633
Employees resign all the time, every year. Right?

182
00:13:53,866 --> 00:13:57,033
I wonder if he'll be able to find a new secretary…

183
00:13:59,566 --> 00:14:01,600
What do you think?

184
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,000
Yes, Boss?

185
00:14:11,066 --> 00:14:15,633
I don't know what to wear to work. Come pick something out for me. That's all.

186
00:14:15,633 --> 00:14:18,366
Wait! Hold on! Hello?

187
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:26,533
Aren't you tired of this, Meow-meow?

188
00:14:26,533 --> 00:14:30,066
Going in circles like this over and over again?

189
00:14:33,733 --> 00:14:35,333
<i>Are you almost here?</i>

190
00:14:35,333 --> 00:14:36,800
<i>Hurry up.</i>

191
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:40,933
Yes! I'm on my way now! If I could fly, I would've flown already!

192
00:14:40,933 --> 00:14:43,366
<i>If you can fly, then fly here now.</i>

193
00:14:55,033 --> 00:14:56,533
Hello.

194
00:14:56,533 --> 00:14:58,000
You're changing the makeup artist?

195
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,904
Why is this being notified so last-minute?

196
00:14:59,904 --> 00:15:02,466
We'd like to keep the original makeup artist that was confirmed.

197
00:15:02,466 --> 00:15:05,230
Otherwise, he might not be available for the interview.

198
00:15:08,233 --> 00:15:09,300
Goody, hi.

199
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:13,700
Yes, there's a meeting this afternoon. All right, see you then. Thank you!

200
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:19,000
I'm here! Just give me a moment.

201
00:15:27,146 --> 00:15:30,066
Let's go with this tie for today, shall we?

202
00:15:30,066 --> 00:15:31,633
Okay.

203
00:16:03,433 --> 00:16:05,233
Perfect.

204
00:16:06,233 --> 00:16:09,119
You're getting pretty used to speaking English these days?

205
00:16:09,119 --> 00:16:11,166
Of course.

206
00:16:11,166 --> 00:16:13,400
No humility at all?

207
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:16,533
Nope. You're the one who taught me, remember?

208
00:16:16,533 --> 00:16:20,733
Humility is just a trick people use when they want to be praised.

209
00:16:45,112 --> 00:16:47,072
What's wrong, Secretary Prim?

210
00:16:47,551 --> 00:16:48,933
Nothing.

211
00:16:48,933 --> 00:16:50,733
That's my water.

212
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:54,000
Sorry!

213
00:16:59,123 --> 00:17:01,300
About what you said this morning.

214
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:03,966
You're resigning because I dragged you out for a run and you got mad.

215
00:17:03,966 --> 00:17:06,133
So, this is payback, right?

216
00:17:06,133 --> 00:17:08,800
- No, that's not it—
- Okay. I get it now.

217
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:11,433
- Get what, exactly?
- I forgive you.

218
00:17:11,433 --> 00:17:12,533
Wait? Forgive me for what?

219
00:17:12,533 --> 00:17:15,866
For being mad at me. I forgive you.

220
00:17:22,433 --> 00:17:24,233
Hello, Pat?

221
00:17:24,233 --> 00:17:27,333
Don't do anything. I'll handle it myself.

222
00:17:28,933 --> 00:17:31,233
I need to borrow 15 minutes from the interview schedule.

223
00:17:31,233 --> 00:17:33,700
I have to deal with a scumbag real quick.

224
00:17:41,966 --> 00:17:44,566
So, you're not resigning anymore. Right?

225
00:17:46,066 --> 00:17:47,766
Perfect!

226
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:33,060
<i>[Lucky Box]</i>

227
00:18:38,870 --> 00:18:40,050
<i>[Thiranon Group]</i>

228
00:18:40,050 --> 00:18:41,060
<i>Was the manager's salary not enough, Mr. Wichai?</i>

229
00:18:41,060 --> 00:18:43,560
Is that why you did this?

230
00:18:43,566 --> 00:18:46,333
I-I…

231
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:49,066
I can explain, Boss.

232
00:18:49,066 --> 00:18:51,300
I really needed the money, Boss. I had no choice…

233
00:18:51,300 --> 00:18:54,233
And who doesn't need money?

234
00:18:54,233 --> 00:18:57,600
That doesn't give you the right to betray the company that's taken care of you.

235
00:18:57,600 --> 00:18:58,533
But, Boss, I…

236
00:18:58,533 --> 00:19:02,266
I'm only giving you a chance because you used to work for my father.

237
00:19:02,266 --> 00:19:04,400
You know what you need to do.

238
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:15,966
Miss Prim, I don't want to resign.

239
00:19:15,966 --> 00:19:18,966
I never meant to embezzle.

240
00:19:18,966 --> 00:19:21,100
It was that damn gambling house…

241
00:19:21,666 --> 00:19:27,000
I mean, no, Miss Prim, I didn't mean to get involved with gambling.

242
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:31,400
A client dragged me in, and I didn't want to play.

243
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:36,988
Please, Miss Prim, talk to him. Help me, please.

244
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,000
Come with me, please.

245
00:19:55,533 --> 00:19:57,600
What's going on, Miss Prim?

246
00:19:57,600 --> 00:20:01,566
You know how much he hates corruption in this organization.

247
00:20:01,566 --> 00:20:03,500
I've already packed up your things.

248
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:05,000
Thank you for your resignation.

249
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,800
Miss Prim…

250
00:20:12,300 --> 00:20:14,800
Please take him to the infirmary.

251
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,310
But if there's any medical cost involved,

252
00:20:16,310 --> 00:20:19,330
make sure he pays for everything himself.

253
00:20:19,333 --> 00:20:20,733
Yes, ma'am.

254
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:27,300
Bhum, the interview team from Asian Tomorrow is here.

255
00:20:27,300 --> 00:20:31,766
Okay! Thank you. Please print out the script I revised, too.

256
00:20:31,766 --> 00:20:33,466
Thank you, thank you.

257
00:20:33,466 --> 00:20:36,666
Prosperity! Go, prosperity! Prosperity, prosperity, prosperity!

258
00:20:36,666 --> 00:20:41,133
Prosperity, prosperity, prosperity! Wealthy!

259
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:44,800
- Prosperity! Prosperity!
- Stop it!

260
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:49,033
Goody, what are you even doing? The interview team is already here!

261
00:20:49,033 --> 00:20:51,600
- Bad luck!
- What bad luck?! What are you talking?

262
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:54,833
Oh my god, where did you even get that holy water bowl from?!

263
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:58,300
I went on a pilgrimage and brought it from the Sacred Kilen Cave Temple!

264
00:20:58,300 --> 00:21:02,800
So our office would thrive and be full of success.

265
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:06,100
But you're wearing a scarf in a cursed color!

266
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:08,800
You're blocking all our good luck and prosperity!

267
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:10,866
Such a bad omen!

268
00:21:10,866 --> 00:21:12,800
Bad omen?! Excuse me?!

269
00:21:12,800 --> 00:21:14,866
Do you know how hard it was to get this scarf?

270
00:21:14,866 --> 00:21:17,466
I bought it at a boutique in Italy for over 10,000 baht!

271
00:21:17,466 --> 00:21:19,966
Wasn't that 250 baht from Sampeng Market?

272
00:21:19,966 --> 00:21:22,059
199, okay?! They gave me a discount.

273
00:21:22,059 --> 00:21:23,166
Taking it off or not?!

274
00:21:23,166 --> 00:21:24,300
Are you nuts? No way!

275
00:21:24,300 --> 00:21:26,733
If you won't take it off, I'll splash you!

276
00:21:26,733 --> 00:21:31,633
What?! Don't! Goody! No!

277
00:21:36,630 --> 00:21:38,433
Oh my god!

278
00:21:39,033 --> 00:21:43,166
What have you done?! What if she gets sick?

279
00:21:43,166 --> 00:21:45,206
You never think before you act!

280
00:21:47,460 --> 00:21:50,200
I'm going to check on the interview now.

281
00:21:51,066 --> 00:21:53,433
Looking good though…

282
00:21:53,433 --> 00:21:55,033
Interview time!

283
00:22:01,966 --> 00:22:05,300
Careful not to catch a cold, okay? We're just worried about you.

284
00:22:12,266 --> 00:22:15,566
Nice. Nice.

285
00:22:19,366 --> 00:22:21,666
- Like a Greek statue!
- Looking good!

286
00:22:28,900 --> 00:22:31,650
Excuse me, Boss, just a little shine on your face.

287
00:22:31,650 --> 00:22:33,660
Allow me to blot it gently.

288
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:40,333
And in case anyone here doesn't already know,

289
00:22:40,333 --> 00:22:42,133
though I do,

290
00:22:42,133 --> 00:22:45,400
our boss here drinks at least two liters of water daily.

291
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:47,800
That's why his skin is so clear, hydrated, and dewy.

292
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:51,433
Honestly, no retouching needed. Right, everyone? So handsome!

293
00:22:51,433 --> 00:22:53,300
Sorry, but who asked?

294
00:22:53,300 --> 00:22:55,800
I wanted to share, is that a problem?!

295
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:58,300
- Done.
- Please, go ahead.

296
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:01,566
Excuse me, move!

297
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:04,666
I'll hold that for you, Miss Bhum.

298
00:23:11,300 --> 00:23:13,900
Okay, I'm ready.

299
00:23:13,900 --> 00:23:16,133
Excuse me, just a moment.

300
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:26,966
Where were you?

301
00:23:27,699 --> 00:23:29,979
Off writing your resignation letter?

302
00:23:32,066 --> 00:23:33,966
I haven't written it yet.

303
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:38,066
Good. Even if you did, I wouldn't approve it.

304
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:44,400
Let's begin, then.

305
00:23:46,866 --> 00:23:49,066
So handsome!

306
00:23:49,066 --> 00:23:53,133
He hasn't even started shooting! Getting ahead of yourself much?

307
00:23:53,133 --> 00:23:54,700
But he is handsome!

308
00:23:54,700 --> 00:23:56,900
Let me begin with the first question.

309
00:23:56,900 --> 00:24:01,033
How do you feel about being named one of Asia's top 5 hottest CEOs?

310
00:24:03,300 --> 00:24:06,466
I've always been hot, so I wouldn't know how I'm supposed to feel.

311
00:24:06,466 --> 00:24:12,633
Oh my gosh, that's a mic-drop answer right there!

312
00:24:12,633 --> 00:24:14,300
Annoying.

313
00:24:14,300 --> 00:24:17,666
We heard that Thiranon Group has expanded into neighboring countries.

314
00:24:17,666 --> 00:24:19,966
How has the response been?

315
00:24:21,700 --> 00:24:25,066
Over the past five years,

316
00:24:25,066 --> 00:24:28,400
across five branches in two countries,

317
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:31,433
we've seen consistent profit growth.

318
00:24:31,433 --> 00:24:32,933
Most recently,

319
00:24:32,933 --> 00:24:38,700
our total profit reached 26.702 billion baht,

320
00:24:38,700 --> 00:24:43,133
a 12.6% increase from the previous year.

321
00:24:43,133 --> 00:24:44,833
That's not correct.

322
00:24:46,066 --> 00:24:52,566
12.6% is the rounded figure. The exact number is 12.58116%.

323
00:24:55,880 --> 00:24:57,470
<i>[12.58116%]</i>

324
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:03,400
Yes, you're right, Boss. That's correct.

325
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:07,266
Also, I believe the fifth branch should be performing better.

326
00:25:07,266 --> 00:25:09,366
We must target Thai craft products,

327
00:25:09,366 --> 00:25:12,300
which have the highest revenue and profit growth.

328
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:15,800
We should allocate more space to that category.

329
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:19,333
Mr. Pat, come up with a plan and present it to me.

330
00:25:19,333 --> 00:25:20,900
Yes, Boss.

331
00:25:20,900 --> 00:25:24,133
If there's nothing else, that's all. Everyone, follow up accordingly.

332
00:25:24,133 --> 00:25:25,833
Thanks, everyone.

333
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:31,410
With your nonstop work schedule,

334
00:25:31,410 --> 00:25:34,630
Mr. Thi, how do you maintain your work-life balance?

335
00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:38,566
I don't have a work-life balance because it's all the same to me.

336
00:25:39,533 --> 00:25:46,000
Work isn't a duty or a burden. It's like breathing in and out.

337
00:25:48,666 --> 00:25:52,466
I can work and relax at the same time.

338
00:26:08,733 --> 00:26:13,600
Work is how I create value in myself. That's who I am.

339
00:26:14,233 --> 00:26:16,666
That was incredible, Boss!

340
00:26:18,533 --> 00:26:21,366
I can't stand fangirls like you, who always squeal over Boss.

341
00:26:21,366 --> 00:26:23,985
- Stop it.
- You're too much.

342
00:26:23,985 --> 00:26:26,300
It's cute.

343
00:26:26,300 --> 00:26:27,700
That?

344
00:26:30,533 --> 00:26:32,966
By the way, have you heard?

345
00:26:33,900 --> 00:26:35,700
Heard what?

346
00:26:45,630 --> 00:26:47,600
Is something going on?

347
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:50,100
Is it true? That you're quitting?

348
00:26:50,100 --> 00:26:52,866
How did you know?

349
00:26:52,866 --> 00:26:54,666
I heard it from her.

350
00:26:55,333 --> 00:26:57,633
I heard it from him.

351
00:26:57,633 --> 00:26:58,966
I heard it from Yong.

352
00:26:58,966 --> 00:27:01,533
But he's not here.

353
00:27:01,533 --> 00:27:05,733
We've been together for nine years, and now you're suddenly running off like this?

354
00:27:05,733 --> 00:27:07,559
It's not sudden, Bhum.

355
00:27:07,559 --> 00:27:09,532
I've thought about it for a while.

356
00:27:09,532 --> 00:27:12,200
Wait, do you have a problem with Boss?

357
00:27:12,900 --> 00:27:15,700
No, it's nothing like that. It's purely a personal decision.

358
00:27:15,700 --> 00:27:20,400
Then where will he find a secretary who gets him like you do?

359
00:27:20,400 --> 00:27:21,666
Exactly!

360
00:27:21,666 --> 00:27:25,666
I don't think he's going to sign that resignation letter easily.

361
00:27:25,666 --> 00:27:28,433
But this is a basic employee right!

362
00:27:28,433 --> 00:27:30,533
Why wouldn't I be allowed to quit?

363
00:27:30,533 --> 00:27:32,833
Either way, I'm resigning.

364
00:27:37,766 --> 00:27:41,766
See! It's your fault, wearing that cursed-colored scarf!

365
00:27:41,766 --> 00:27:44,266
That's why Prim is quitting. Take it off now!

366
00:27:44,266 --> 00:27:45,940
You failed every logic test in school?

367
00:27:45,940 --> 00:27:47,290
What does my scarf relate to this?

368
00:27:47,295 --> 00:27:49,366
- Take it off or not?
- Nope.

369
00:27:49,366 --> 00:27:50,800
- If you don't…
- What?

370
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:54,066
The two of us… are going to strip you down.

371
00:27:54,066 --> 00:27:55,866
- What?!
- Take it off! Bhum!!

372
00:27:55,866 --> 00:27:59,533
- Take it off! Take it off right now!
- Don't you dare come near me!

373
00:28:01,966 --> 00:28:04,566
So annoying! What's wrong with you, sis?!

374
00:28:04,566 --> 00:28:07,000
I just don't get it. Why would Prim resign?

375
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:11,066
Is it because she's overworked and can't take it anymore?

376
00:28:11,066 --> 00:28:13,466
Poor thing.

377
00:28:14,333 --> 00:28:17,400
Are you feeling sorry, or are you happy?

378
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:18,433
Happy about what?

379
00:28:18,433 --> 00:28:21,973
Well, now you can offer to be her replacement.

380
00:28:21,973 --> 00:28:26,900
Come on, I know your every intention inside and out!

381
00:28:26,900 --> 00:28:29,066
Oh, stop! Calm down!

382
00:28:29,066 --> 00:28:32,566
I might want to be the assistant to the Vice President

383
00:28:32,566 --> 00:28:35,366
so I can be close to my idol.

384
00:28:35,366 --> 00:28:36,610
But it doesn't mean I'd stoop so low

385
00:28:36,610 --> 00:28:38,730
as to cut someone else's legs off for it!

386
00:28:38,733 --> 00:28:43,266
That's right. It's a good thing. Being an assistant like Prim is exhausting.

387
00:28:43,266 --> 00:28:46,466
She barely has time to eat with us.

388
00:28:46,466 --> 00:28:49,266
If you took the job, you wouldn't have time to shop.

389
00:28:49,266 --> 00:28:52,600
I can shop online!

390
00:28:52,600 --> 00:28:55,666
But seriously, if Prim resigns,

391
00:28:55,666 --> 00:29:00,500
the new assistant can only be

392
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:05,266
perfectly well-mannered, talented, charming,

393
00:29:05,266 --> 00:29:11,700
and with an excellent attitude like Manchuporn Thakingsak, me!

394
00:29:15,166 --> 00:29:17,166
You're too much.

395
00:29:21,500 --> 00:29:24,666
Salary's in!

396
00:29:24,666 --> 00:29:26,066
Bonus, too!

397
00:29:26,066 --> 00:29:29,433
Now I can buy gifts for Phon!

398
00:29:29,433 --> 00:29:32,433
Wait, his name is Phon?

399
00:29:32,433 --> 00:29:34,733
Salary is equal to spoiling the guy.

400
00:29:34,733 --> 00:29:36,333
- Spoil the guy, spoil the guy.
- Always!

401
00:29:36,333 --> 00:29:38,510
I'm in such a good mood, and with this bonus,

402
00:29:38,510 --> 00:29:42,400
I should buy food for Prim!

403
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:43,860
No need to go yourself, Ms. Bhum.

404
00:29:43,860 --> 00:29:47,060
I'll go buy it. Please enjoy your meal.

405
00:29:47,633 --> 00:29:49,333
Thank you!

406
00:29:51,633 --> 00:29:56,033
Girl, the way he cares for you is so sweet.

407
00:29:56,033 --> 00:29:58,483
Even if you don't get the Vice President,

408
00:29:58,483 --> 00:30:00,333
you'll get Yong instead!

409
00:30:00,333 --> 00:30:02,266
- So cute!
- Thank you!

410
00:30:02,266 --> 00:30:04,900
You're welcome! What now?

411
00:30:04,900 --> 00:30:09,024
Stop it. Stop pushing this. Use your brain cells for something else!

412
00:30:09,024 --> 00:30:11,285
- Just open your heart!
- Open my heart for what?

413
00:30:11,285 --> 00:30:13,566
Remember? You used to like me back when I played soccer.

414
00:30:13,566 --> 00:30:19,333
Peeking, glancing, I saw it. You liked me when I looked a bit manly.

415
00:30:19,333 --> 00:30:20,966
You fooled me so well back then!

416
00:30:20,966 --> 00:30:24,066
"Hi there, I'm off to play soccer." "Am I cool or what?"

417
00:30:24,066 --> 00:30:26,933
- The world's ending!
- Open your heart!

418
00:30:26,933 --> 00:30:29,200
<i>[The house mortgage has been fully redeemed.]</i>

419
00:30:29,200 --> 00:30:35,366
<i>[Ms. Primala, you can come to the bank to collect the deed now.]</i>

420
00:30:44,220 --> 00:30:45,700
<i>[Bonus Salary]</i>

421
00:30:56,621 --> 00:30:58,521
Are you satisfied?

422
00:31:01,533 --> 00:31:03,166
Excuse me?

423
00:31:03,166 --> 00:31:06,566
The bonus I gave you, are you satisfied with it?

424
00:31:07,100 --> 00:31:09,500
Thank you very much, Boss.

425
00:31:09,500 --> 00:31:11,833
Do you have any tasks for me?

426
00:31:11,833 --> 00:31:15,333
No tasks. But I do have a proposal for you.

427
00:31:15,933 --> 00:31:17,633
A proposal?

428
00:31:17,633 --> 00:31:20,666
I'm going to raise your salary. You'll also get a personal driver,

429
00:31:20,666 --> 00:31:23,400
move to a condo closer to the office,

430
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:26,366
and I'll give you company shares. Sounds good?

431
00:31:26,366 --> 00:31:29,833
Is all of this just so I don't quit?

432
00:31:29,833 --> 00:31:31,360
Yes.

433
00:31:31,833 --> 00:31:34,933
- Then I have to decline.
- What?

434
00:31:34,933 --> 00:31:38,433
I've already made up my mind to resign, so I will.

435
00:31:41,033 --> 00:31:45,166
<i>I worked so hard on this plan, and it's not working?</i>

436
00:31:47,600 --> 00:31:49,733
Can I at least get a reason?

437
00:31:50,300 --> 00:31:53,170
I want to live a different kind of life.

438
00:31:53,170 --> 00:31:55,233
Different how?

439
00:31:55,233 --> 00:31:58,300
The kind I've never lived before.

440
00:31:58,300 --> 00:31:59,906
But…

441
00:32:04,666 --> 00:32:07,840
Hello? You've arrived?

442
00:32:07,840 --> 00:32:09,330
Okay.

443
00:32:10,733 --> 00:32:15,166
We'll talk about this later. Right now, come have lunch with my parents.

444
00:32:15,166 --> 00:32:19,466
But isn't that a private family meal?

445
00:32:19,466 --> 00:32:22,092
My family can include you, too.

446
00:32:22,092 --> 00:32:23,866
See you downstairs.

447
00:32:39,300 --> 00:32:43,300
This new restaurant was inspired by a tugboat transporting sand.

448
00:32:43,300 --> 00:32:46,600
It serves Michelin-level Thai cuisine in perfect bite-sized portions,

449
00:32:46,600 --> 00:32:51,233
with over a hundred dishes rotating adorably on a conveyor belt.

450
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:56,200
Good idea! Tourists will love this.

451
00:32:56,200 --> 00:33:03,044
If this branch does well, you should open the next one in Phuket.

452
00:33:05,066 --> 00:33:09,400
Prim, dear, try the pomelo salad. It's delicious.

453
00:33:09,400 --> 00:33:11,159
Yes, ma'am.

454
00:33:18,254 --> 00:33:21,833
Why didn't you bring your girlfriend, Jinny?

455
00:33:21,833 --> 00:33:22,900
Why would I?

456
00:33:22,900 --> 00:33:25,033
Well, aren't you and Jinny…?

457
00:33:25,033 --> 00:33:27,266
Jinny and I aren't dating, Dad.

458
00:33:27,266 --> 00:33:28,433
What?

459
00:33:28,433 --> 00:33:30,933
Oh, stop saying "what" over and over again.

460
00:33:30,933 --> 00:33:32,666
How can I not be confused?

461
00:33:32,666 --> 00:33:36,100
You're always out and about with her.

462
00:33:36,100 --> 00:33:38,300
What do you call that then?

463
00:33:39,300 --> 00:33:41,900
Talking stage, right, Prim?

464
00:33:44,766 --> 00:33:47,600
Really, what's there to talk about that much?

465
00:33:47,600 --> 00:33:52,066
Jinny is the daughter of Minister Damrong.

466
00:33:52,766 --> 00:33:57,166
She's a good match. Just get married already.

467
00:33:57,166 --> 00:34:02,966
Don't meddle in the kid's personal life so much.

468
00:34:05,433 --> 00:34:12,066
If she's not his girlfriend, I may push Prim into the race instead.

469
00:34:13,666 --> 00:34:14,666
I'm sorry.

470
00:34:14,666 --> 00:34:18,833
You're being ridiculous. That's not possible.

471
00:34:24,166 --> 00:34:27,666
Prim, you see Jinny a lot, don't you?

472
00:34:27,666 --> 00:34:30,800
Help encourage things between her and him a bit.

473
00:34:33,633 --> 00:34:37,000
I'd rather not interfere in his matters.

474
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:40,400
Besides, I'm planning to resign.

475
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:43,966
- What? Resign?!
- What? Resign?!

476
00:34:43,966 --> 00:34:45,533
Yes.

477
00:34:51,133 --> 00:34:54,766
So, why do you want to leave?

478
00:34:55,800 --> 00:34:59,000
Is it because you hate me? Is that it?

479
00:34:59,933 --> 00:35:02,300
I don't hate you.

480
00:35:03,747 --> 00:35:05,547
Then why?

481
00:35:07,333 --> 00:35:10,400
I said tell me. That's an order!

482
00:35:11,033 --> 00:35:12,700
I want to live my life.

483
00:35:12,700 --> 00:35:14,766
I want to be Primala, not just "Secretary Prim"

484
00:35:14,766 --> 00:35:18,066
whose entire life revolves around work and you nearly every day.

485
00:35:18,066 --> 00:35:20,366
You might see work as your breath,

486
00:35:20,366 --> 00:35:22,166
but it's not like that for others.

487
00:35:22,166 --> 00:35:25,233
I genuinely appreciate the bonus and all the offers you made.

488
00:35:25,233 --> 00:35:27,266
But what I want isn't what you're offering.

489
00:35:27,266 --> 00:35:29,366
What I want is my life.

490
00:35:29,366 --> 00:35:31,933
I'll continue working until the end of next month.

491
00:35:31,933 --> 00:35:35,386
If you don't let me quit, I'll tell the Labor Department.

492
00:35:35,386 --> 00:35:37,000
Excuse me.

493
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:38,726
Goodbye.

494
00:35:54,266 --> 00:35:56,300
<i>[Thai BBQ]</i>

495
00:35:56,300 --> 00:35:59,066
So that means…

496
00:35:59,066 --> 00:36:01,900
Does that mean we got the house back?

497
00:36:01,900 --> 00:36:03,652
Yes.

498
00:36:09,900 --> 00:36:12,466
Prim, did you pay a lot this time?

499
00:36:12,466 --> 00:36:14,800
Why didn't you tell me? I could've helped.

500
00:36:14,800 --> 00:36:18,566
What would you help with? Just save your money for Ploen's tuition.

501
00:36:18,566 --> 00:36:21,300
Besides, the last payment wasn't that expensive,

502
00:36:21,300 --> 00:36:23,400
just paying off the interest.

503
00:36:23,400 --> 00:36:28,300
Dad, seriously. He partnered with those awful friends and lost the house.

504
00:36:28,300 --> 00:36:31,933
If Mom were still here, she would've snapped his neck for sure!

505
00:36:31,933 --> 00:36:35,166
Look at what he's put you through for all these years.

506
00:36:35,966 --> 00:36:37,566
Don't blame Dad.

507
00:36:37,566 --> 00:36:40,233
